ing%2C%20Deputy%20Assistant%20Attorney%20General%20Eric%20Hamilton%20repeatedly%20said%20that%20the%20Pentagon%20questions%20Anthropic's%20%26quot%3Breliability%20and%20trustworthiness.%26quot%3B%20Hamilton%20said%20that%20defense%20officials%20are%20concerned%20Anthropic%20may%20try%20to%20improperly%20skew%20its%20AI%20models%20or%20shut%20off%20access.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20weeks%2C%20Hegseth%2C%20who%20met%20with%20Amodei%2C%20said%20the%20AI%20startup%20put%20%26quot%3BSilicon%20Valley%20ideology%20above%20American%20lives.%26quot%3B%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20decried%20the%20%26quot%3BWOKE%20COMPANY%26quot%3B%20run%20by%20%26quot%3B%20Leftwing%20nut%20jobs%26quot%3B%20in%20a%20Truth%20Social%20post%20that%20was%20also%20part%20of%20the%20California%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTheir%20selfishness%20is%20putting%20AMERICAN%20LIVES%20at%20risk%2C%20our%20Troops%20in%20danger%2C%20and%20our%20National%20Security%20in%20JEOPARDY%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20wrote%20on%20Truth%20Social%20on%20February%2027.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjudge-blocks-anthropic-supply-chain-risk-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774568198000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c55d2e48461c18d7be65ff%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjudge-blocks-anthropic-supply-chain-risk-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Anthropic%20has%20said%20it%20could%20lose%20billions%20if%20a%20federal%20judge%20didn't%20step%20in%20to%20block%20the%20Trump%20administration.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bgriffiths%40insider.com%20(Brent%20D.%20Griffiths%2CLloyd%20Lee)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjudge-blocks-anthropic-supply-chain-risk-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trump's%20signature%20to%20appear%20on%20US%20currency%2C%20a%20first%20for%20a%20sitting%20president%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Donald%20Trump%20walks%20in%20the%20White%20House%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c5b5374133f63e1c778d67%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222560%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDonald%20Trump%20will%20be%20the%20first%20sitting%20president%20in%20US%20history%20to%20have%20his%20signature%20on%20the%20nation's%20currency.%3Cp%3EBRENDAN%20SMIALOWSKI%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPresident%20Trump%20will%20be%20the%20first%20sitting%20US%20president%20to%20have%20his%20signature%20on%20the%20nation's%20currency.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20move%20is%20symbolic%20of%20the%20nation's%20%26quot%3Bfiscal%20strength%26quot%3B%20under%20Trump%2C%20the%20Treasury%20announced%20Thursday.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESince%20Trump%20took%20office%2C%20the%20dollar%20has%20fallen%20amid%20sweeping%20tariffs%20and%20global%20conflict.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-borrowers-moving-to-treasury-whats-next-debt-repayment-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETreasury%20Department%3C%2Fa%3E%20announced%20Thursday%20that%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20signature%20will%20appear%20on%20future%20US%20paper%20currency%2C%20marking%20the%20first%20time%20a%20sitting%20president's%20name%20will%20be%20printed%20on%20American%20bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETreasury%20Secretary%20Scott%20Bessent%2C%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhome.treasury.gov%2Fnews%2Fpress-releases%2Fsb0425%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20framed%20the%20move%20as%20symbolic%2C%20saying%20US%20currency%20should%20reflect%20the%20country's%20economic%20standing%20under%20Trump's%20leadership%20and%20serve%20as%20a%20marker%20of%20the%20nation's%20%26quot%3Bfiscal%20strength%20and%20stability.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20breaks%20with%20long-standing%20precedent.%20For%20more%20than%20a%20century%2C%20US%20banknotes%20have%20carried%20the%20signatures%20of%20Treasury%20officials%20%E2%80%94%20not%20the%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Treasury%20said%20the%20move%20was%20to%20commemorate%20the%20coming%20250th%20anniversary%20of%20American%20independence%2C%20as%20the%20administration%20pursues%20a%20broader%20effort%20to%20mark%20the%20milestone%20through%20currency%20and%20coin%20redesigns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20bills%20bearing%20Trump's%20signature%2C%20along%20with%20that%20of%20the%20Treasury%20Secretary%2C%20will%20begin%20being%20issued%20at%20the%20semiquincentennial%2C%20the%20Treasury%20said.%20It's%20unclear%20which%20bills%20will%20bear%20Trump's%20signature%20or%20how%20long%20the%20initiative%20is%20expected%20to%20last.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20decision%20for%20Trump%20to%20end%20years%20of%20precedent%20of%20Treasury%20Secretaries%20signing%20bills%20is%20another%20piece%20of%20evidence%20that%20Trump%20is%20trying%20to%20brand%20everything%20in%20his%20name%2C%20even%20though%20it%20is%20unusual%20and%20in%20the%20mold%20of%20what%20more%20undemocratic%20leaders%20typically%20do%20in%20other%20countries%2C%26quot%3B%20Christian%20Grose%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20political%20science%20and%20public%20policy%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Southern%20California%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrose%20said%20the%20move%20risks%20making%20using%20cash%20a%20partisan%20act%2C%20potentially%20making%20Trump's%20supporters%20more%20enthusiastic%20about%20cash%20payments%2C%20and%20Democrats%20more%20likely%20to%20use%20electronic%20payments.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20dollar%20has%20faced%20downward%20pressure%20in%20recent%20months%2C%20driven%20in%20part%20by%20sweeping%20tariffs%20that%20have%20rattled%20global%20trade%20and%20increased%20import%20costs%2C%20as%20wel